ActImmigration and Refugee Protection Act
PrecisRegulations Amending the IMMIGRATION AND REFUGEE PROTECTION REGULATIONS to the extent that seafarers entering Canada in order to join the crew of a ship will be required to have a valid passport as well as a seafarer's identity document, and if required, a temporary resident visa, effective June 11, 2003.
